ay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkZlOTdhMTVhNC0zYTE2LTQ5MzctODAwYi04YTVmODJjYzdiNjNfNTAweDY0NS5qcGVn 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/QTBAPiwL_ 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux." width="262" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/6P0lsxwIdbX-mtovSLSYxOYMnH-NF4dONJh7sYYcftc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkZlOTdhMTVhNC0zYTE2LTQ5MzctODAwYi04YTVmODJjYzdiNjNfNTAweDY0NS5qcGVn 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/lbyYk7hXkBJNipKCOHjO- 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/_MiZBwm2IXA_jbGeFBs1g6kvZR9KvAlI_7PZUTEWtZQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGZTk3YTE1YTQtM2ExNi00OTM3LTgwMGItOGE1ZjgyY2M3YjYzXzUwMHg2NDUuanBlZw== 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p><strong>The Clapper</strong>. When this outlet hears sounds at the right frequency separated by the right interval, it switches on or off. It was first sold in 1984 and as far as I can tell hasn’t been significantly updated since except to add a Bob Ross module. (Yes, this really exists. It gives quotes when you clap three times.) ($20)</p><p>I’m confused. The Clapper seems to work fine. Why isn’t it more popular? I <em>think</em> it’s partly that it was originally marketed as an aid to the infirm and elderly rather than Retro Home Automation for Your Active Lifestyle. But why aren’t there new variants? The <a href="https://patents.google.com/patent/US5493618" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">patent</a> is long expired, but there seem to be few (and bad) competitors. There are even rumors that quality has declined for brand-name Clappers.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3b44ffea-3fc5-463e-9b9a-b3e9ab48f70d_500x361.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/JrdpLv6f5YtH3-fCs1HnUQ-zV0MtiO5wBuMRwv10-y0=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkYzYjQ0ZmZlYS0zZmM1LTQ2M2UtOWI5YS1iM2U5YWI0OGY3MGRfNTAweDM2MS5qcGVn 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Vke06UE3JtzMh_j8tWKkRSTJqD0v6Iqsi7L-yXNmfEo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkYzYjQ0ZmZlYS0zZmM1LTQ2M2UtOWI5YS1iM2U5YWI0OGY3MGRfNTAweDM2MS5qcGVn 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Oc4Pz5T_ 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/e5E-- 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Nz8cWT3wla28khCv4brbbj11ldn6_PClvjsNO5fqm-I=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGM2I0NGZmZWEtM2ZjNS00NjNlLTliOWEtYjNlOWFiNDhmNzBkXzUwMHgzNjEuanBlZw==" width="278" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux. 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ROasjzzF6qCHHPRWHvq8aB5N- 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Nz8cWT3wla28khCv4brbbj11ldn6_PClvjsNO5fqm-I=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGM2I0NGZmZWEtM2ZjNS00NjNlLTliOWEtYjNlOWFiNDhmNzBkXzUwMHgzNjEuanBlZw== 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p><strong>Motorized shades/blinds with physical remotes</strong>. If you look at reviews for IKEA’s shades or blinds, there are many complaints about trying to pair them with a hub and phone. But you don’t need a hub! They come with a physical remote and there’s physical process to control how far they drop. Though sadly you lose the ability to set daily schedule or program them to move randomly and scare your dog. ($130-infinity)</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F95bf39d4-fb0b-4011-a903-1769f1812af9_500x545.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ZR_DODxUouTcI4cAuyzRv6jLpE4qAQiX5T4zWM7Mq_s=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY5NWJmMzlkNC1mYjBiLTQwMTEtYTkwMy0xNzY5ZjE4MTJhZjlfNTAweDU0NS5qcGVn 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/HydZ_Af6siKVvsxX_ 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/jU6aX2DQLtKkOQC4rYkYyTJbuS5j-" width="238" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/dSXuDL1cZCrd8o5eh_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Kvp4Box7RNGCgcP8G_JaQjx81yr_lI_P_RpYlOabGtY=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGOTViZjM5ZDQtZmIwYi00MDExLWE5MDMtMTc2OWYxODEyYWY5XzUwMHg1NDUuanBlZw== 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/jU6aX2DQLtKkOQC4rYkYyTJbuS5j- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p><strong>Mechanical outlet timers</strong>: You plug this into an outlet, it slowly spins once per day, and the pins determine is the outlet is active for each 30 minute period. ($5-10)</p><p>This! This is the kind of thing I need more of in my life! I <em>really</em> think it deserves to be more celebrated as a triumph of design. But it’s existed for decades and I can’t find the original inventor.</p><p>Many use these with light for plants. Or, it can be nice to wake up with light rather than sound. Instead of buying a light alarm clock, you can just plug a lamp into one of these. Or, if you buy into the rationalist trend of <em>very bright</em> lights, then you can rig up one of these up and have each day greet you with 100k lumens gently screaming into your face.</p><p>Or, in winter, I use a (<a href="https://dynomight.nethumidifiers/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">non-ultrasonic</a>) humidifier. But it’s only really useful for a couple of hours before going to bed, after which humans provide plenty of humidity. Using a timer automates things, saves energy, and avoids humidity getting out of control in the middle of the night. Even better, it reduces how often you need to refill the tank.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff95e08c2-b5f9-4858-a924-624b0e3b6d75_500x852.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/4g6H-03hebP5dJkcBBMIfJk421YHUE3yf-wuCWR21gM=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLm